node.text: Welcome to our new series, Rampe It Up, where @ameliarampe takes an ingredient you probably already have in your pantry, and shows you how to level it up at home! node.text: @kiacooks credits her mom and grandma for instilling in her a love of good food and cooking, and in today’s episode of Secret Family Recipe, Kia makes one of her grandma’s signature dishes, Chicken & Stuff, with an assist from her mom. Along the way, Kia tweaks things here and there (blanched green beans instead of canned; sautéed chicken instead of boiled) to make the recipe her own while she and her mom talk about the origins of this delicious dish with the whimsical name. Tap the link in our bio for Kia’s family recipe. #thekitchn

node.title: Secret Family Recipe: Chicken & Stuff with @kiacooks

node.text: If you’ve spent even just 2 minutes on this app recently, you’ve likely seen no fewer than 3,359 different grazing tables and cheese boards in your feed. Yes, they are trendy with a capital T, but how do you actually set one up? What food should you buy? Where should you put your first pile? And the second? And, good gosh, how do you even know if you’ll have enough food? Take a deep breath. We’re here to help. Tap the link in our bio for our printable templates, which can turn anyone into a charcuterie champ! (Video: @joe.lingeman, Styling: @jesseszewczyk) #thekitchn
